  "question_text": "<h3>Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree</h3><p>Design an algorithm to serialize and deserialize a binary tree.</p>",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Tree.",
  "output_format": "Deep Copy Tree.",
  "constraints": [
    "nodes <= 10^4"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use pre-order traversal. For serialization, append node values or \"null\" to a list. For deserialization, use a recursive helper that consumes elements from the list one by one.",
  "answer": "class Codec:\n    def serialize(self, root):\n        def dfs(node):\n            if not node: res.append(\"null\"); return\n            res.append(str(node.val))\n            dfs(node.left)\n            dfs(node.right)\n        res = []\n        dfs(root); return \",\".join(res)\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n        def dfs():\n            val = next(vals)\n            if val == \"null\": return None\n            node = TreeNode(int(val))\n            node.left = dfs(); node.right = dfs()\n            return node\n        vals = iter(data.split(\",\"))\n        return dfs()",
